g.text: Inheritance tree of super classes starting from package

a.title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).

a.title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.
a.xlink:title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.

a.title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.

a.title: ― UnitType: Unit type is a type or class of objects of interest (units).
a.xlink:title: ― UnitType: Unit type is a type or class of objects of interest (units).

a.title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.
a.xlink:title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.

a.title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].

a.title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.
a.xlink:title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.

a.title: ― ConceptualDomain: Set of concepts, where each concept is intended to be used as the meaning (signified) for a datum.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualDomain: Set of concepts, where each concept is intended to be used as the meaning (signified) for a datum.

a.title: ― SentinelConceptualDomain: Conceptual domain of sentinel concepts.
a.xlink:title: ― SentinelConceptualDomain: Conceptual domain of sentinel concepts.

a.title: ― SubstantiveConceptualDomain: Conceptual domain of substantive concepts.
a.xlink:title: ― SubstantiveConceptualDomain: Conceptual domain of substantive concepts.

a.title: ― ConceptualValue: Concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived which is associated to a single data instance.
